eqlTagTable.name: eqlTagTable
eqlTagTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the list of tags. For every tag, there is a row in this table. This table supports multiple types of tags. Initially the only supported tag type is 'folder'. Subsequently clients can add other types of tags, and clients can add tags of the new tag types to this table. Clients can walk this table to get all tags, or can maintain the first index constant (tag type) to get all tags type. For example, the client can walk this table to get all folder tags.

eqlTagEntry.name: eqlTagEntry
eqlTagEntry.description: An entry in the tag table.

eqlTagType.name: eqlTagType
eqlTagType.description: This field specifies the type of this tag. A typical tag type is folder. Tag type enumeration values from 0 to 9,999 are reserved for internal use. When user defined tag types are supported, the user defined tag enumerated values start at 10,000.

eqlTagIndex.name: eqlTagIndex
eqlTagIndex.description: The index of the tag, included only because the MIB compiler fails without it, so this is a workaround.

eqlTagRowStatus.name: eqlTagRowStatus
eqlTagRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqlTagValue.name: eqlTagValue
eqlTagValue.description: This field specifies the value of the tag. For folders, this value is the name of the folder. The tag value can be up to 63 characters plus NULL.

eqlTagAdminAccountKey.name: eqlTagAdminAccountKey
eqlTagAdminAccountKey.description: This field specifies the unique key for identifying a volume administrator that owns this tag. If no account has this value as its eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountKey, then the tag is unassigned.

eqlTagValueDescription.name: eqlTagValueDescription
eqlTagValueDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details about this tag. The description can be up to 127 characters plus NULL.

eqlTagObjectTable.name: eqlTagObjectTable
eqlTagObjectTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains an association between tags and objects. Clients can use this table to determine for a given tag, which objects are associated with the tag. When the tag is a folder, it lists the objects that are in the folder.

eqlTagObjectEntry.name: eqlTagObjectEntry
eqlTagObjectEntry.description: An entry in the tag object table.

eqlTagObjectIndex.name: eqlTagObjectIndex
eqlTagObjectIndex.description: The index of the tag to object, included only because the MIB compiler fails without it, so this is a workaround.

eqlTagObjectTaggedObjectPointer.name: eqlTagObjectTaggedObjectPointer
eqlTagObjectTaggedObjectPointer.description: The authoritative identification for the MIB object to tag.

eqlTagObjectRowStatus.name: eqlTagObjectRowStatus
eqlTagObjectRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqlAdminAccountTagTable.name: eqlAdminAccountTagTable
eqlAdminAccountTagTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic This table has a row for every admin that has read or read-write access to a tag. If an admin does not have access to tag X, there is no row in the table with index 1.admin.X. Clients can walk this table to get all tags that an admin can access.

eqlAdminAccountTagEntry.name: eqlAdminAccountTagEntry
eqlAdminAccountTagEntry.description: An entry in the tag table.

eqlAdminAccountTagAccess.name: eqlAdminAccountTagAccess
eqlAdminAccountTagAccess.description: The administrative permission to a tag.

eqlVolumeTagTable.name: eqlVolumeTagTable
eqlVolumeTagTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Stores which tags reference a particular volume. Clients can walk this table, and for each volume, get the tags that reference this volume.

eqlVolumeTagEntry.name: eqlVolumeTagEntry
eqlVolumeTagEntry.description: An entry in the volume tag table.

eqlVolumeTagValue.name: eqlVolumeTagValue
eqlVolumeTagValue.description: This field specifies the value of the tag. For folders, this value is the name of the folder. The tag value can be up to 63 characters plus NULL.
